WEBVTT

00:14.161 --> 00:16.132
[glass shatters] ‐ One was definitely
calling Muldoon.

00:16.132 --> 00:17.401
I saw him run away.

00:17.401 --> 00:19.138
‐ The Lam kid
fucking cut our traps.

00:19.138 --> 00:20.808
‐ The gall
of that goddamn family.

00:20.808 --> 00:23.480
‐ Percy was really scared
that somebody was after her‐‐

00:23.480 --> 00:24.550
some guy.

00:24.550 --> 00:25.785
There had been a fight,

00:25.785 --> 00:27.656
and the room
was all smashed up.

00:27.656 --> 00:29.125
‐ She called on me,

00:29.125 --> 00:30.662
and I went with Colin
to pick her up.

00:30.662 --> 00:32.331
‐ You went, too?

00:32.331 --> 00:33.400
‐ Let it go.

00:33.400 --> 00:35.505
‐ If you're investigating
anyone, it should be him.

00:35.505 --> 00:37.576
‐ I think this case
is bringing out

00:37.576 --> 00:40.347
a really ugly side of you.

00:40.347 --> 00:43.353
[eerie music]

00:43.353 --> 00:46.292
♪ ♪

00:48.129 --> 00:51.302
[dramatic music]

00:51.302 --> 00:58.283
♪ ♪

01:06.499 --> 01:09.472
[somber music]

01:09.472 --> 01:11.610
♪ ♪

01:11.610 --> 01:13.146
‐ Steady.

01:13.146 --> 01:15.551
‐ There we go.

01:15.551 --> 01:18.824
[indistinct chatter]

01:18.824 --> 01:21.697
‐ Yeah, watch that end.

01:21.697 --> 01:22.866
Okay, got it.

01:22.866 --> 01:30.247
♪ ♪

01:57.234 --> 01:59.271
‐ I watched her grow up.

02:01.644 --> 02:02.912
‐ They're here.

02:02.912 --> 02:04.650
‐ Meg, we already ID'd her.

02:04.650 --> 02:05.752
I really don't think‐‐

02:05.752 --> 02:07.922
She was in the water
for almost a week.

02:07.922 --> 02:09.693
You don't want to see her
like this.

02:09.693 --> 02:12.699
[dramatic music]

02:12.699 --> 02:19.646
♪ ♪

02:54.415 --> 02:56.219
‐ Here they come.

03:02.431 --> 03:05.538
‐ I'm so sorry
it came to this, Meg.

03:05.538 --> 03:08.410
Uh...

03:08.410 --> 03:09.646
let me...

03:15.858 --> 03:19.298
Uh, Tom here is from Rockport,

03:19.298 --> 03:22.237
and, uh, he examined the body‐‐

03:22.237 --> 03:24.408
uh, her body,

03:24.408 --> 03:28.951
and he didn't find ev‐‐
evidence of any foul play.

03:28.951 --> 03:30.655
She died from the fall.

03:33.393 --> 03:35.732
Now, we can send her
to Portland‐‐

03:35.732 --> 03:38.002
to the labs, but...

03:38.002 --> 03:40.440
‐ We don't expect to find
anything to the contrary.

03:40.440 --> 03:43.714
‐ But we can do
whatever you want, Meg.

03:43.714 --> 03:46.754
Keep this investigation open.

03:46.754 --> 03:48.423
It's up to you.

03:49.526 --> 03:51.563
‐ We should start
planning the funeral.

03:53.868 --> 03:56.573
We need her body.

03:56.573 --> 03:58.209
We need this to be over.

04:07.595 --> 04:08.764
‐ What's this?

04:08.764 --> 04:10.768
‐ It's a Celtic North Star.

04:10.768 --> 04:13.039
Fishermen love their totems.

04:13.039 --> 04:16.479
That one's a big one
for the Irish.

04:16.479 --> 04:18.884
It points you to Heaven...

04:18.884 --> 04:20.688
and fish.

04:20.688 --> 04:23.828
‐ Excuse me, where was that?

04:23.828 --> 04:25.631
‐ In her jacket pocket.

04:25.631 --> 04:28.671
[dramatic music]

04:28.671 --> 04:31.743
♪ ♪

04:31.743 --> 04:33.012
‐ Valerie.

04:33.012 --> 04:35.785
Does that name
mean anything to you?

04:35.785 --> 04:36.887
‐ No.

04:36.887 --> 04:42.732
♪ ♪

04:44.636 --> 04:46.405
‐ I know there's more.

04:46.405 --> 04:48.443
The guy
in the surveillance footage‐‐

04:48.443 --> 04:49.913
someone was with her
on the bluff.

04:49.913 --> 04:52.852
♪ ♪

04:52.852 --> 04:56.359
Family, whatever that is...

04:56.359 --> 04:58.463
name on the back of the star.

04:59.933 --> 05:01.469
The star.

05:03.439 --> 05:05.545
Why would you have that
with you?

05:06.814 --> 05:09.385
‐ Does it even matter?

05:09.385 --> 05:10.922
I mean, you saw what you saw.

05:10.922 --> 05:12.491
I jumped.

05:13.561 --> 05:14.930
‐ Ah, come on.

05:14.930 --> 05:17.735
It's not that simple.

05:17.735 --> 05:19.639
‐ But it was my choice.

05:21.442 --> 05:24.481
What if I really
didn't want to live anymore?

05:27.120 --> 05:30.060
You know that feeling.

05:30.962 --> 05:34.636
Those times at Sonya's
when you couldn't sleep...

05:36.540 --> 05:38.611
Or when you were
on the ferry coming here,

05:38.611 --> 05:41.082
you were looking down
into the water,

05:41.082 --> 05:43.587
thinking about sinking.

05:43.587 --> 05:45.390
How much longer
you can keep this up?

05:45.390 --> 05:52.539
♪ ♪

06:01.890 --> 06:04.563
‐ How did it go?

06:04.563 --> 06:06.733
‐ Ah, it's over with.

06:06.733 --> 06:10.440
‐ Well, at least
they can stop wondering.

06:10.440 --> 06:13.479
At least they have an answer.

06:13.479 --> 06:15.985
‐ But there's still
a lot of questions.

06:15.985 --> 06:18.991
And, uh,
they're closing the case.

06:18.991 --> 06:22.497
No one wants to keep looking.

06:22.497 --> 06:25.470
‐ I can understand that.

06:25.470 --> 06:28.577
It's less painful that way.

06:31.683 --> 06:34.455
‐ Maybe they don't want
something exposed.

06:37.595 --> 06:41.168
‐ We should go, leave.

06:43.006 --> 06:45.811
Oh, we could drive
down the coast.

06:45.811 --> 06:49.853
Won't feel like much
of a vacation after all this.

06:49.853 --> 06:51.489
‐ Yeah.

06:51.489 --> 06:53.761
This is where
you wanted to paint.

06:53.761 --> 06:54.629
I mean, it has the light

06:54.629 --> 06:56.767
that you were
looking forward to and...

06:56.767 --> 06:59.038
‐ Well,
there's light other places.

06:59.038 --> 07:01.910
‐ [sighs] And...

07:01.910 --> 07:03.580
is Greta‐‐

07:03.580 --> 07:06.920
I mean,
you've hardly seen her at all.

07:06.920 --> 07:09.091
‐ Why don't you want to go?

07:09.091 --> 07:11.863
‐ I...

07:11.863 --> 07:14.769
‐ What is it about Percy?

07:14.769 --> 07:17.474
‐ [mutters softly]

07:22.552 --> 07:25.190
‐ [inhales sharply]

07:25.190 --> 07:27.662
[exhales shakily]

07:27.662 --> 07:30.433
You're right.
We should go.

07:31.970 --> 07:34.709
Really, I‐‐

07:34.709 --> 07:36.713
You're right.

07:38.082 --> 07:40.721
‐ Okay.

07:40.721 --> 07:42.090
Okay.

07:42.090 --> 07:45.096
I think it's better
for both of us, huh?

07:45.096 --> 07:52.177
♪ ♪

07:54.949 --> 07:57.922
[soft drum beats]

07:57.922 --> 08:00.928
[eerie tone]

08:00.928 --> 08:07.909
♪ ♪

08:13.587 --> 08:17.762
[seagulls calling]

08:17.762 --> 08:24.609
♪ ♪

09:00.748 --> 09:02.719
‐ Excuse me.

09:05.023 --> 09:08.329
‐ Just trying to figure out
who this boat belongs to.

09:08.329 --> 09:10.300
‐ Well, it's private property.

09:10.300 --> 09:13.306
I'm gonna need you
to get back on the docks.

09:13.306 --> 09:15.343
‐ It's a Muldoon boat,
though, right?

09:15.343 --> 09:17.114
I know Sean's boat,

09:17.114 --> 09:20.253
but this Colin's boat?

09:20.253 --> 09:22.658
‐ Yeah.

09:22.658 --> 09:25.096
‐ Percy work on this boat?

09:25.096 --> 09:27.802
‐ Not recently.

09:27.802 --> 09:30.641
‐ She worked on Colin's crew.

09:30.641 --> 09:33.045
‐ Uh, not exactly.

09:33.045 --> 09:34.749
‐ How do you mean?

09:37.053 --> 09:39.726
‐ Well, they used to go out
together a lot on their own.

09:41.663 --> 09:43.166
‐ So it wasn't fishing trips.

09:43.166 --> 09:44.869
Any idea what it was?

09:49.344 --> 09:51.081
‐ My job is to monitor
the docks,

09:51.081 --> 09:52.819
not what people do out there.

09:52.819 --> 09:55.390
Just stay off the boats, okay?

09:55.390 --> 09:57.060
‐ Sure, okay.

09:59.933 --> 10:04.174
[ominous music]

10:04.174 --> 10:08.015
[door opens]

10:08.015 --> 10:11.021
[door closes]

10:11.021 --> 10:18.035
♪ ♪

10:44.722 --> 10:46.392
‐ There's nothing
any of us can say

10:46.392 --> 10:49.264
that'll change things.

10:49.264 --> 10:51.435
I'm in this fight,

10:51.435 --> 10:53.874
and I'm not backing down.

10:55.376 --> 10:57.915
And I'm gonna do
whatever it takes.

10:57.915 --> 11:00.888
♪ ♪

11:00.888 --> 11:02.892
‐ I see Colin
has joined us tonight.

11:02.892 --> 11:04.194
It's nice to see you
back, Colin.

11:04.194 --> 11:06.398
The floor is yours if you‐‐
if you want it.

11:06.398 --> 11:08.269
‐ Thanks, Owen.

11:08.269 --> 11:09.973
Um...

11:09.973 --> 11:12.010
I know I haven't been
the most, uh,

11:12.010 --> 11:14.147
steady member here.

11:14.147 --> 11:16.385
Uh, I've probably taken

11:16.385 --> 11:19.291
all of you for granted
sometimes...

11:19.291 --> 11:21.161
most times.
[scoffs]

11:21.161 --> 11:24.434
I mean, you guys know...

11:24.434 --> 11:26.305
Percy and me.

11:26.305 --> 11:29.444
[chuckles]

11:29.444 --> 11:31.883
We were like the same person.

11:34.187 --> 11:36.893
[chuckling]
She drove me fucking crazy.

11:38.329 --> 11:41.268
We, uh...

11:41.268 --> 11:44.041
had this big fight, uh...

11:44.041 --> 11:45.310
just before she...

11:45.310 --> 11:49.418
♪ ♪

11:49.418 --> 11:53.292
You know, did what she did,
and, uh...

11:53.292 --> 11:55.063
we weren't talking.

11:55.063 --> 11:57.467
♪ ♪

11:57.467 --> 12:00.941
Anyway, all I know is,
fuck, I want a drink.

12:00.941 --> 12:02.778
[chuckles]

12:02.778 --> 12:06.352
♪ ♪

12:06.352 --> 12:09.057
God knows I loved her.

12:11.462 --> 12:14.067
And when I think
about that last time...

12:14.067 --> 12:19.144
♪ ♪

12:19.144 --> 12:22.017
And what I did,

12:22.017 --> 12:23.452
it's, uh...

12:23.452 --> 12:30.801
♪ ♪

12:57.253 --> 12:59.859
[cell phone buzzing]
‐ [whispering]
I think that's...

12:59.859 --> 13:01.863
I'll talk to you later.

13:08.543 --> 13:11.281
Thanks for meeting me.

13:11.281 --> 13:13.319
I realize things
didn't end so well

13:13.319 --> 13:16.158
at dinner the other night.

13:16.158 --> 13:19.031
‐ I stirred the pot.

13:19.031 --> 13:20.466
I'm not a good guest.

13:20.466 --> 13:23.974
‐ Percy didn't do this
to herself.

13:23.974 --> 13:26.245
Someone's to blame for this.

13:28.550 --> 13:32.023
‐ You sure?
‐ Percy was devout.

13:32.023 --> 13:34.027
She knew that wasn't an option.

13:34.027 --> 13:36.900
She would have come
to me first.

13:36.900 --> 13:39.906
‐ That book at your house
that you showed me

13:39.906 --> 13:42.043
and the objects
that were in her room‐‐

13:42.043 --> 13:44.014
something
was turning inside her‐‐

13:44.014 --> 13:45.216
‐ That's what I mean.

13:45.216 --> 13:47.187
That wasn't Percy.

13:47.187 --> 13:50.360
Somebody had control over her.

13:50.360 --> 13:54.134
Everyone‐‐even my sons‐‐
they want to give up.

13:54.134 --> 13:56.806
Somebody did this to her.

13:59.579 --> 14:01.916
‐ Does the name Valerie
mean anything to you?

14:01.916 --> 14:03.452
‐ Valerie, who's that?

14:03.452 --> 14:05.924
‐ Was she one
of Percy's friends?

14:05.924 --> 14:09.331
Or could she have been somebody
that was on the payroll?

14:09.331 --> 14:11.301
‐ No one I know.
Why?

14:14.107 --> 14:16.278
‐ I'm just guessing.

14:18.082 --> 14:21.956
‐ You don't let
things go easily.

14:21.956 --> 14:23.894
That's why I need your help.

14:29.204 --> 14:30.908
‐ I have to leave tomorrow.

14:32.945 --> 14:35.216
‐ Oh, already?

14:35.216 --> 14:38.222
[dramatic music]

14:38.222 --> 14:41.161
♪ ♪

14:41.161 --> 14:45.403
Can't you stay
just for a few more days?

14:45.403 --> 14:47.107
You've done so much already.

14:47.107 --> 14:51.983
♪ ♪

14:51.983 --> 14:54.121
‐ [sighs]
I can't.

14:54.121 --> 15:01.268
♪ ♪

15:06.980 --> 15:10.253
‐ I want you to know that
if you ever want to come back,

15:10.253 --> 15:11.990
it's an open invitation.

15:11.990 --> 15:14.127
It doesn't expire.

15:14.127 --> 15:15.463
‐ Well, then maybe

15:15.463 --> 15:18.703
you can keep your eyes and ears
open for me.

15:18.703 --> 15:21.643
‐ Harry...
‐ It's just not sitting right.

15:21.643 --> 15:22.678
‐ How do you mean?

15:22.678 --> 15:25.016
‐ We don't know who was
on that bluff with her.

15:25.016 --> 15:27.320
The objects that she had‐‐

15:27.320 --> 15:29.291
they were so specific.

15:29.291 --> 15:30.727
And the star‐‐

15:30.727 --> 15:33.567
she brought that star
out there.

15:33.567 --> 15:36.004
It's like she was trying
to tell us something.

15:36.004 --> 15:38.442
‐ Harry, enjoy your retirement.

15:38.442 --> 15:40.179
I got it from here.

15:40.179 --> 15:41.683
‐ Sorry to keep you waiting.

15:41.683 --> 15:43.385
‐ Hi, Stephanie, how are you?
‐ Hey.

15:43.385 --> 15:46.024
Uh, you know...

15:46.024 --> 15:48.663
Uh, is it true about Percy?

15:48.663 --> 15:50.266
‐ Yeah.

15:54.542 --> 15:57.013
‐ No words for losing a child.

15:59.451 --> 16:01.589
‐ So what'll you have, Harry?
Uh, sky's the limit‐‐

16:01.589 --> 16:03.593
‐ Actually, uh,
we're having a, uh‐‐

16:03.593 --> 16:05.496
a kitchen issue.

16:05.496 --> 16:08.503
Chowder okay?
It's all we can serve.

16:08.503 --> 16:11.008
‐ Sounds good to me.
‐ Okay, thank you.

16:11.008 --> 16:16.686
♪ ♪

16:16.686 --> 16:18.990
‐ Ah Maah would be so
disgusted with you right now.

16:18.990 --> 16:22.463
‐ [speaking Cantonese]

16:22.463 --> 16:24.201
‐ At least she doesn't
let people walk all over her.

16:24.201 --> 16:26.471
‐ [speaking Cantonese]

16:26.471 --> 16:28.475
‐ Look, I don't care
if I made things worse.

16:28.475 --> 16:30.246
It's about having
a pair of balls.

16:30.246 --> 16:31.381
‐ [speaking Cantonese]

16:31.381 --> 16:33.085
‐ [speaking Cantonese]

16:33.085 --> 16:35.624
‐ [speaking Cantonese]

16:35.624 --> 16:37.595
‐ And I fucking loved it, okay?

16:37.595 --> 16:39.197
‐ CJ.

16:39.197 --> 16:41.468
[speaking Cantonese]

16:45.076 --> 16:48.082
[ominous music]

16:48.082 --> 16:49.351
‐ It's okay.

16:49.351 --> 16:52.090
It's just
a broken refrigerator.

16:52.090 --> 16:59.304
♪ ♪

17:00.206 --> 17:03.078
‐ CJ.

17:03.078 --> 17:05.116
It's quite a mess in there.

17:05.116 --> 17:06.418
What happened?

17:06.418 --> 17:09.525
‐ Someone broke
into our kitchen last night...

17:09.525 --> 17:11.596
fucked the coolant coils
in our storage fridges.

17:11.596 --> 17:13.567
Both those units
need to be replaced.

17:13.567 --> 17:15.303
We'll be bleeding money
for weeks .

17:15.303 --> 17:17.473
‐ Payback
for the lobster traps?

17:19.579 --> 17:22.116
Look, I'm not pursuing this.

17:22.116 --> 17:23.520
I'm out of here in a few days.

17:23.520 --> 17:26.593
It's just something
that I heard.

17:26.593 --> 17:28.663
‐ You know, the Muldoons‐‐

17:28.663 --> 17:31.401
they get away
with whatever they want.

17:31.401 --> 17:33.405
And my dad just takes it
over and over.

17:33.405 --> 17:34.675
At least I did something.

17:34.675 --> 17:37.247
‐ The Muldoons
keep this going with you.

17:37.247 --> 17:39.685
Why is that?

17:39.685 --> 17:41.488
‐ It's Colin.

17:41.488 --> 17:43.425
He's looking
for someone to blame

17:43.425 --> 17:45.664
because he's the guilty one.

17:45.664 --> 17:47.367
‐ Too much from you today.

17:47.367 --> 17:49.672
‐ Enough of this shit, Dad.

17:49.672 --> 17:51.709
Okay?
You know it's true.

17:51.709 --> 17:53.780
Tell him what you saw.
He's listening.

17:55.383 --> 17:58.289
‐ Mike, what did you see?

17:58.289 --> 18:02.430
♪ ♪

18:02.430 --> 18:04.835
‐ They took his boat out a lot,

18:04.835 --> 18:06.873
just the two of them.

18:06.873 --> 18:09.712
‐ Where are you going?

18:11.181 --> 18:14.588
[indistinct arguing]

18:14.588 --> 18:20.801
♪ ♪

18:20.801 --> 18:22.403
Okay?

18:22.403 --> 18:23.873
Okay?

18:23.873 --> 18:26.345
[inaudible]

18:26.345 --> 18:30.453
♪ ♪

18:30.453 --> 18:33.192
There's something wrong
with him and her.

18:33.192 --> 18:34.829
‐ Yeah.

18:36.866 --> 18:39.170
Thanks.
‐ Mm.

18:41.776 --> 18:43.345
‐ Thanks, CJ.

18:43.345 --> 18:48.222
♪ ♪

18:48.222 --> 18:51.161
‐ [speaking Cantonese]

19:02.551 --> 19:09.699
♪ ♪

19:15.644 --> 19:18.516
‐ That's a nice idea,
but we cannot do that.

19:18.516 --> 19:19.685
‐ Why not?

19:19.685 --> 19:21.522
People open restaurants
every day.

19:21.522 --> 19:23.425
‐ [scoffs]
People with money.

19:23.425 --> 19:25.262
You think they pay us enough
to do that?

19:25.262 --> 19:26.699
‐ Come on, Mom.

19:26.699 --> 19:28.803
Think big.
Just start with a name.

19:28.803 --> 19:32.243
‐ The Lam Seafood Restaurant.
‐ That's so boring.

19:32.243 --> 19:33.513
‐ So boring?

19:33.513 --> 19:34.682
‐ Okay, how about, um‐‐

19:34.682 --> 19:36.385
how about
The Golden Fish?

19:36.385 --> 19:37.755
‐ [speaking Cantonese]

19:37.755 --> 19:39.792
‐ Golden Fish?
[speaking Cantonese]

19:39.792 --> 19:41.529
‐ Yeah, you know,
like koi fish.

19:41.529 --> 19:43.800
Doesn't that stand
for prosperity or something?

19:43.800 --> 19:45.804
‐ Oh, very good.

19:45.804 --> 19:48.242
‐ 'Cause you see, when white
people see "The Golden Fish,"

19:48.242 --> 19:49.678
they just think
of fried food, right?

19:49.678 --> 19:51.783
Golden fried fish.
‐ [laughs]

19:51.783 --> 19:54.287
See? This one
is the marketing expert.

19:54.287 --> 20:01.502
♪ ♪

20:05.844 --> 20:08.817
‐ I got scallops
for our last supper

20:08.817 --> 20:12.423
and a pound of shrimp,
so I hope you're hungry.

20:12.423 --> 20:14.662
I think I overbought.

20:20.540 --> 20:27.688
♪ ♪

21:02.791 --> 21:05.964
[music intensifies]

21:05.964 --> 21:12.845
♪ ♪

21:20.760 --> 21:22.029
‐ Is that, uh, all you saw,
was the... red raincoat?

21:22.029 --> 21:23.833
‐ That's all I needed to see.

21:23.833 --> 21:26.506
‐ Was there any markings on it
or any stains or anything?

21:26.506 --> 21:28.776
‐ No, I did‐‐
I just edged to the door

21:28.776 --> 21:30.045
and ran out.

21:30.045 --> 21:31.516
‐ When you were outside,

21:31.516 --> 21:33.418
did you see any movement
around the doors?

21:33.418 --> 21:34.420
‐ No‐‐I just‐‐

21:34.420 --> 21:36.959
I wasn't about
to wait around and say hello.

21:36.959 --> 21:38.963
‐ Yeah, sure.

21:38.963 --> 21:41.536
I'm just gonna do
a quick survey,

21:41.536 --> 21:42.704
see what they touched.

21:42.704 --> 21:44.909
‐ Where were you?

21:44.909 --> 21:46.813
‐ I went long with Lou,

21:46.813 --> 21:48.883
and then I was
talking to the Lams.

21:48.883 --> 21:50.620
‐ About Percy?

21:52.858 --> 21:55.396
This‐‐this brings up
a lot for me.

21:55.396 --> 21:57.534
A‐a‐an intruder in the house?

21:57.534 --> 21:58.903
A lot.

21:58.903 --> 22:01.909
[sighs]

22:01.909 --> 22:03.947
‐ What can I do?

22:03.947 --> 22:06.418
‐ I want to be
on the first ferry out of here

22:06.418 --> 22:07.721
tomorrow morning.

22:07.721 --> 22:10.727
[dramatic music]

22:10.727 --> 22:17.875
♪ ♪

22:52.811 --> 22:54.882
‐ C‐‐

22:54.882 --> 22:59.390
Can you just give me
a couple days?

22:59.390 --> 23:02.698
I'll wrap things up,
and then I'll come find you.

23:06.004 --> 23:07.908
I can't walk away from this.

23:07.908 --> 23:09.878
I can't.

23:09.878 --> 23:11.616
‐ Yeah, you can.

23:11.616 --> 23:13.620
It's just a‐a choice.

23:15.055 --> 23:18.028
‐ Not for me.

23:18.028 --> 23:21.769
‐ Yeah, for you, too.

23:21.769 --> 23:23.071
There's a version of you

23:23.071 --> 23:26.378
that gets on the ferry
right now.

23:28.081 --> 23:31.454
This thing
that makes you so persistent,

23:31.454 --> 23:32.891
it's‐‐

23:32.891 --> 23:35.864
it's beautiful.

23:35.864 --> 23:38.770
I‐it's also what
makes you obsessive.

23:38.770 --> 23:41.007
‐ I know. I know.

23:44.180 --> 23:48.589
‐ But you‐‐you still can't
get on the boat with me?

23:48.589 --> 23:54.133
♪ ♪

23:54.133 --> 23:57.874
‐ I wouldn't be able
to live with that...

23:57.874 --> 23:59.745
With myself.

24:01.214 --> 24:04.755
Just a few more days,
that's‐‐right?

24:04.755 --> 24:09.632
‐ I don't think that I can
keep going on like this.

24:12.804 --> 24:14.207
'Cause you‐‐you are forever

24:14.207 --> 24:17.614
trying to make up
for something.

24:20.687 --> 24:22.156
‐ I know. I‐‐

24:25.129 --> 24:27.668
[ferry whistle blows]

24:27.668 --> 24:29.137
‐ Okay, okay.

24:29.137 --> 24:35.617
♪ ♪

24:35.617 --> 24:37.053
‐ Sonya...

24:38.690 --> 24:39.958
‐ I'll be fine.

24:39.958 --> 24:44.233
♪ ♪

24:44.233 --> 24:46.204
[ferry whistle blows]

24:46.204 --> 24:49.110
♪ ♪

24:49.110 --> 24:51.214
‐ There's still time.

24:51.214 --> 24:54.722
♪ ♪

24:54.722 --> 24:57.193
You can get on that boat
and leave right now.

24:57.193 --> 25:03.973
♪ ♪

25:03.973 --> 25:06.211
[bell tolling]

25:06.211 --> 25:09.217
[ominous music]

25:09.217 --> 25:16.565
♪ ♪

25:48.763 --> 25:51.301
‐ Harry?

25:51.301 --> 25:54.173
I thought you'd be
on the first ferry out of here.

25:54.173 --> 25:56.946
‐ I decided to stay
a few extra days.

25:56.946 --> 25:58.215
‐ Oh, that's good.

25:58.215 --> 26:01.254
You and Sonya
can enjoy the island a bit.

26:01.254 --> 26:03.325
‐ Actually, it's just me.

26:03.325 --> 26:04.928
[indistinct chatter]

26:04.928 --> 26:06.632
‐ Oh.

26:10.774 --> 26:13.311
‐ Is Sean okay?

26:13.311 --> 26:16.919
‐ Oh, gosh, poor guy.

26:16.919 --> 26:18.723
Had a moment at the podium.

26:18.723 --> 26:21.327
Started blaming himself
and everyone for Percy.

26:21.327 --> 26:22.931
Colin had to bring him down.

26:22.931 --> 26:25.937
[dramatic music]

26:25.937 --> 26:32.951
♪ ♪

26:42.203 --> 26:45.109
[dramatic music] [indistinct chatter]

26:45.109 --> 26:52.323
♪ ♪

27:29.297 --> 27:31.367
‐ She was a natural
on the boats.

27:33.873 --> 27:35.877
‐ So you two
were friends, huh?

27:35.877 --> 27:39.885
‐ No, just, um,
came to pay my respects.

27:39.885 --> 27:42.924
The Muldoons would notice
if I didn't.

27:47.166 --> 27:50.172
[indistinct chatter]

27:50.172 --> 27:57.353
♪ ♪

27:59.758 --> 28:02.429
[inaudible]

28:02.429 --> 28:09.745
♪ ♪

28:12.316 --> 28:14.086
‐ Hey, Sean.

28:14.086 --> 28:15.823
‐ Thought you left.

28:15.823 --> 28:18.128
‐ Didn't make sense
not to be here.

28:18.128 --> 28:20.432
‐ Now that you are,
you might as well eat up.

28:20.432 --> 28:23.238
Everyone else is.

28:23.238 --> 28:25.910
‐ Yeah, this can be hard times.

28:29.050 --> 28:31.989
‐ Why do you think that is?

28:31.989 --> 28:34.828
I mean, what exactly...

28:34.828 --> 28:35.930
makes it hard?

28:35.930 --> 28:38.268
You tell me.

28:38.268 --> 28:40.840
All day long,
they've been coming up,

28:40.840 --> 28:42.309
saying sorry.

28:43.478 --> 28:46.184
Look all surprised like...

28:46.184 --> 28:49.457
some kind of accident took her,
like they didn't see it coming.

28:52.162 --> 28:54.735
‐ You think they did?

28:56.337 --> 28:58.943
‐ As far as
Percy's concerned...

29:00.780 --> 29:03.485
You're the only innocent person
in this house.

29:07.126 --> 29:09.965
‐ What are you saying?

29:09.965 --> 29:13.038
You think
they did something to her?

29:13.038 --> 29:16.010
‐ Sometimes all you got to do
to be guilty

29:16.010 --> 29:17.981
is look the other way.

29:17.981 --> 29:22.189
♪ ♪

29:22.189 --> 29:25.362
No one wants to hear that
from me.

29:25.362 --> 29:27.366
‐ Hey.

29:28.536 --> 29:30.105
‐ You out of here already?

29:30.105 --> 29:32.242
‐ Got to prep the boat
for tomorrow.

29:32.242 --> 29:33.512
Bring it in.

29:33.512 --> 29:40.359
♪ ♪

29:42.296 --> 29:43.899
All right,
I'll see you later, yeah?

29:43.899 --> 29:45.469
‐ Yeah.

29:49.143 --> 29:52.917
[indistinct chatter]

29:52.917 --> 29:59.865
♪ ♪

30:01.100 --> 30:02.904
‐ You stayed.

30:04.574 --> 30:08.048
‐ Uh, yeah, for a few days.

30:08.048 --> 30:09.183
‐ Sonya?

30:12.189 --> 30:13.993
‐ Nah.

30:15.062 --> 30:18.134
‐ Well, you look like
you could use a drink.

30:21.842 --> 30:23.612
[liquor pours, glass clinks]

30:23.612 --> 30:26.952
See this groove
in the floor here?

30:26.952 --> 30:29.624
My mother used to
pace back and forth

30:29.624 --> 30:31.427
in front of that window

30:31.427 --> 30:34.333
whenever my father
was on a long haul.

30:34.333 --> 30:38.943
I used to sit and watch her
from this couch right here.

30:38.943 --> 30:41.582
I swore to myself
I'd never be a pacing woman,

30:41.582 --> 30:43.953
but after today...

30:43.953 --> 30:45.556
here I am.

30:47.594 --> 30:49.898
‐ Know that feeling.

30:52.469 --> 30:56.244
Last night somebody broke into
the house where I'm staying.

30:56.244 --> 30:57.981
I'm sorting that out.

30:57.981 --> 31:00.419
‐ Did you see them?
‐ No, I wasn't there.

31:00.419 --> 31:03.659
But they looked
through my stuff.

31:03.659 --> 31:06.965
I bet they were trying to see
what I found out.

31:06.965 --> 31:09.938
‐ That means there really is
somebody out there.

31:09.938 --> 31:12.209
Do you have any idea
who it could be?

31:15.182 --> 31:19.056
‐ Did Colin him visit Percy
when she lived in Portland?

31:20.425 --> 31:22.897
‐ Why do you keep
going back to this?

31:25.268 --> 31:28.374
‐ So you're sure that
they didn't have any contact

31:28.374 --> 31:30.011
at that point?

31:30.011 --> 31:32.483
‐ No, Colin would have told me.

31:34.654 --> 31:37.226
‐ Seems like they
were very close.

31:39.263 --> 31:40.933
‐ Yeah.

31:40.933 --> 31:44.641
Colin and Percy
have always been close.

31:44.641 --> 31:47.146
She took to him
from the start.

31:47.146 --> 31:51.154
He was a better father to her
than her own dad ever was.

31:51.154 --> 31:53.158
What are you implying?

31:53.158 --> 31:56.532
♪ ♪

31:56.532 --> 31:58.536
Colin would never.

31:58.536 --> 32:00.606
[footsteps departing]

32:00.606 --> 32:04.447
♪ ♪

32:04.447 --> 32:06.250
‐ You realize whoever it is,

32:06.250 --> 32:09.423
there's a good chance
it'll be someone you know...

32:09.423 --> 32:12.029
[glass clinks]

32:12.029 --> 32:14.366
r close to someone you know.

32:14.366 --> 32:16.672
♪ ♪

32:16.672 --> 32:18.174
‐ Whatever you find,

32:18.174 --> 32:20.646
I'd appreciate you
coming to me first.

32:23.051 --> 32:26.357
‐ He said
he couldn't get a lead on it.

32:26.357 --> 32:28.461
‐ Well, I thought this guy
was an expert or something.

32:28.461 --> 32:30.065
Isn't that what Seth said?

32:30.065 --> 32:32.604
‐ Yeah, but the guy says
none of it looks familiar.

32:32.604 --> 32:34.741
He couldn't link it to anyone
besides Percy.

32:34.741 --> 32:38.481
‐ There's got to be someone
else involved in all this.

32:38.481 --> 32:40.285
‐ I don't know
what to tell you.

32:40.285 --> 32:42.489
Anyway, I‐I didn't want
to leave it at her place,

32:42.489 --> 32:45.095
so I put it on your boat
in the hold.

32:45.095 --> 32:46.598
‐ What?
‐ Well, I wasn't about

32:46.598 --> 32:48.468
to bring all that stuff here.

32:48.468 --> 32:50.038
‐ Did anyone see you?

32:50.038 --> 32:51.207
‐ No.

32:51.207 --> 32:53.044
‐ [sighs] All right.

32:53.044 --> 32:56.450
I'll go over after
this winds down and pick it up.

32:56.450 --> 32:57.720
Damn it.

32:57.720 --> 33:00.660
[eerie music]

33:00.660 --> 33:08.041
♪ ♪

33:38.434 --> 33:41.642
[clattering]

33:41.642 --> 33:44.614
[suspenseful music]

33:44.614 --> 33:47.286
♪ ♪

33:47.286 --> 33:50.258
[engine turning over]

33:50.258 --> 33:57.206
♪ ♪

34:07.794 --> 34:11.300
[motor rumbling][rumbling stops]

34:11.300 --> 34:13.539
[lock clicks]

34:13.539 --> 34:16.812
[dramatic music]

34:16.812 --> 34:24.159
♪ ♪

35:07.847 --> 35:10.285
‐ So you're searching
my boat now?

35:12.189 --> 35:14.561
‐ Trying to get
the whole picture.

35:16.497 --> 35:19.537
‐ Why'd you ask my mom
about Valerie?

35:21.340 --> 35:23.879
‐ So you know who she is?
‐ I'll ask the questions.

35:23.879 --> 35:25.850
Who told you that name?

35:27.219 --> 35:31.227
‐ You probably noticed
the star that was there‐‐

35:31.227 --> 35:33.364
she had it with her
when she died.

35:33.364 --> 35:35.836
That name‐‐
she carved it on the back,

35:35.836 --> 35:39.176
so must've been
pretty important to her.

35:41.147 --> 35:43.351
Why was that?

35:43.351 --> 35:45.455
‐ How the fuck should I know?

35:48.796 --> 35:51.635
That's all you got
after all this time?

35:52.904 --> 35:56.712
‐ I do know
that Percy looked up to you.

35:56.712 --> 36:00.853
I was told she wouldn't say no
to anything that you wanted.

36:03.525 --> 36:05.796
But then after you
brought her back from Portland,

36:05.796 --> 36:07.466
something turned.

36:07.466 --> 36:09.537
♪ ♪

36:09.537 --> 36:12.877
‐ You have no idea what
the fuck you're talking about.

36:12.877 --> 36:15.448
‐ After you brought her back,

36:15.448 --> 36:19.490
people saw you go out
on your boat a lot.

36:19.490 --> 36:22.797
‐ And what do you think
I did to her?

36:22.797 --> 36:26.571
♪ ♪

36:26.571 --> 36:28.909
‐ I think you loved Percy...

36:30.478 --> 36:32.917
Maybe a little too much.

36:34.219 --> 36:37.492
People were worried about her
in your company.

36:38.896 --> 36:39.998
And your mother, too.

36:39.998 --> 36:42.537
♪ ♪

36:42.537 --> 36:44.273
She said,
"No, nothing went on,"

36:44.273 --> 36:46.545
but I could see in her eyes,
something happened.

36:46.545 --> 36:47.680
She was scared.

36:47.680 --> 36:54.694
♪ ♪

36:54.694 --> 36:57.667
‐ [sniffs]

36:57.667 --> 37:00.940
You can't possibly imagine
because you don't know God.

37:00.940 --> 37:02.944
Someone like you...

37:05.448 --> 37:07.252
You don't believe in anything.

37:07.252 --> 37:09.858
♪ ♪

37:09.858 --> 37:12.797
I was helping her.

37:12.797 --> 37:15.368
‐ Do you not tremble
before me?

37:15.368 --> 37:18.642
I placed the sand
as the boundary for the sea...

37:18.642 --> 37:22.717
a perpetual barrier
that it cannot pass.

37:22.717 --> 37:26.591
Though the waves toss,
they cannot prevail.

37:26.591 --> 37:29.697
Though they roar,
they cannot pass over it.

37:31.601 --> 37:33.839
‐ Come on, one more time.

37:33.839 --> 37:36.010
‐ I'm tired.

37:36.010 --> 37:37.747
‐ You used to take
this seriously.

37:37.747 --> 37:39.751
‐ I don't get the point.
I don't feel anything.

37:39.751 --> 37:42.355
‐ It's not about feeling.

37:42.355 --> 37:45.361
It's about repetition,
prayer.

37:45.361 --> 37:47.466
I‐i‐it can‐‐it can break
you down, I get it,

37:47.466 --> 37:49.904
but it builds you back up...

37:49.904 --> 37:51.340
helps you unlock your will.

37:51.340 --> 37:54.480
All the power you need...

37:54.480 --> 37:56.450
right here.

37:58.020 --> 38:02.028
‐ It seems hypocritical,
like it's only about you.

38:02.028 --> 38:04.032
‐ It's about your relationship
with Him,

38:04.032 --> 38:06.337
and that's what's broken
in you.

38:07.607 --> 38:08.374
Hey, hey, hey.

38:08.374 --> 38:11.046
Come on, come on,
come on, come on.

38:11.046 --> 38:14.353
I thought we were a team,
you and me.

38:17.660 --> 38:19.363
‐ We are.

38:20.733 --> 38:22.637
‐ Okay, well, then...

38:24.841 --> 38:26.645
Don't let us down.

38:26.645 --> 38:30.786
♪ ♪

38:30.786 --> 38:32.657
Okay?

38:32.657 --> 38:33.926
‐ [sniffles]

38:33.926 --> 38:40.539
♪ ♪

38:40.539 --> 38:44.614
both: I placed the sand
as the boundary for the sea...

38:44.614 --> 38:47.587
‐ A perpetual barrier
that it cannot pass.

38:47.587 --> 38:49.356
‐ I thought I could reach her,

38:49.356 --> 38:52.563
but someone else
had gotten there first.

38:52.563 --> 38:59.511
♪ ♪

39:03.819 --> 39:06.791
You scared the shit out of me.

39:06.791 --> 39:08.595
What's going on?

39:09.964 --> 39:11.835
Are you okay?

39:11.835 --> 39:18.849
♪ ♪

39:18.849 --> 39:21.453
‐ Can I stay here tonight?

39:21.453 --> 39:24.928
‐ Why are you soaking wet, huh?

39:24.928 --> 39:27.065
‐ I just need a place to sleep.

39:28.869 --> 39:30.639
‐ Okay.

39:30.639 --> 39:33.579
Okay, um,
let's get you a hot shower.

39:33.579 --> 39:35.081
Okay?

39:36.718 --> 39:38.454
‐ Don't tell Grams.

39:38.454 --> 39:41.861
‐ I didn't realize it then,
but she was already gone.

39:41.861 --> 39:43.464
Percy.

39:45.769 --> 39:48.407
You too good
to pick up your phone now?

39:50.044 --> 39:51.480
You think you can just
blow me off?

39:51.480 --> 39:52.817
I waited on the boat
for, like, an hour.

39:52.817 --> 39:55.154
‐ I don't want to do it
anymore‐‐it doesn't work.

39:55.154 --> 39:57.927
‐ What, are you
fucking drawing now?

39:57.927 --> 40:01.066
You kidding me?

40:01.066 --> 40:04.139
What the fuck
is going on with you?

40:04.139 --> 40:05.876
You know you're making
Grams sick, right?

40:05.876 --> 40:07.747
She's a fucking basket case
because of you.

40:07.747 --> 40:09.617
‐ That's her fault, not mine.
‐ What did you just say?

40:09.617 --> 40:10.485
Her fault?

40:10.485 --> 40:12.890
You hear yourself right now?

40:12.890 --> 40:15.495
You realize all the bullshit
we went through because of you?

40:15.495 --> 40:17.132
Well, fine!
Don't come crawling back to me

40:17.132 --> 40:18.635
next time you need help!
‐ I won't!

40:18.635 --> 40:19.938
‐ You're an ungrateful
fucking bitch.

40:19.938 --> 40:22.142
You realize that?

40:22.142 --> 40:24.914
I raised you.

40:24.914 --> 40:26.518
‐ No one asked you to.

40:26.518 --> 40:28.922
You're not my fucking dad.

40:28.922 --> 40:35.736
♪ ♪

40:39.142 --> 40:41.313
‐ I could have gone
easier on her.

40:44.186 --> 40:46.891
Percy didn't want
to be saved anymore.

40:49.764 --> 40:51.200
She made her choice.

40:51.200 --> 40:55.809
♪ ♪

40:55.809 --> 40:57.947
‐ Choice about what?

40:57.947 --> 40:59.817
‐ Oh, you want to see?

40:59.817 --> 41:01.655
Fine, I'll show you.

41:03.959 --> 41:05.495
This shit.

41:07.533 --> 41:09.236
Look at this.
Look at it.

41:09.236 --> 41:10.471
There's a ton of it.

41:10.471 --> 41:11.975
I mean, what is that?

41:11.975 --> 41:14.012
What is this shit?

41:14.012 --> 41:15.683
Huh?
What is that?

41:17.018 --> 41:18.822
Look me in the eye

41:18.822 --> 41:22.963
and tell me someone didn't
poison her mind with that shit.

41:22.963 --> 41:25.234
It wasn't me.

41:25.234 --> 41:28.107
‐ What it was is you filled
her head with what you wanted,

41:28.107 --> 41:30.979
and you couldn't stand to
share her with somebody else.

41:30.979 --> 41:32.583
‐ No.

41:32.583 --> 41:33.852
No!

41:33.852 --> 41:38.127
♪ ♪

41:38.127 --> 41:39.997
‐ [shouts]

41:39.997 --> 41:44.006
♪ ♪

41:44.006 --> 41:46.978
‐ God damn it!

41:46.978 --> 41:49.951
[engine turning over]

41:49.951 --> 41:52.690
♪ ♪

42:01.708 --> 42:03.578
[dramatic music] ‐ Fuck.
[keys clatter]

42:03.578 --> 42:05.181
Oh, God.

42:05.181 --> 42:06.618
[groans]

42:06.618 --> 42:08.789
[breathing heavily]

42:08.789 --> 42:12.830
♪ ♪

42:12.830 --> 42:17.238
Z, E...

42:17.238 --> 42:18.575
G.

42:18.575 --> 42:25.589
♪ ♪

42:27.560 --> 42:30.164
‐ Are you sure you even
remember what you saw?

42:34.306 --> 42:36.043
It was an A here.

42:38.314 --> 42:39.917
I remember.

42:39.917 --> 42:45.596
♪ ♪

42:45.596 --> 42:47.800
‐ A.

42:47.800 --> 42:49.604
Wba...

42:49.604 --> 42:52.308
Zegwa...

42:52.308 --> 42:55.314
Zegwba.

42:55.314 --> 42:56.584
Zeg‐‐

42:56.584 --> 42:58.087
♪ ♪

42:58.087 --> 43:01.126
‐ The Bazegw legend tells
the story of DuPair,

43:01.126 --> 43:03.598
an Irish settler
on Hanover Island.

43:03.598 --> 43:05.936
♪ ♪

43:05.936 --> 43:08.240
‐ Bazegw.

43:08.240 --> 43:09.844
Bazegw.

43:09.844 --> 43:12.348
♪ ♪

43:12.348 --> 43:14.854
Bazegw.

43:14.854 --> 43:16.858
Bazegw Point.

43:16.858 --> 43:23.972
♪ ♪

44:42.830 --> 44:45.836
[ominous music]

44:45.836 --> 44:52.783
♪ ♪
